metadata.name: Wooded Solitude #30
metadata.description:
"Wooded Solitude" is an exploration of my love for crystals, architecture, being one with nature, escaping technology and becoming ok with the idea of being alone. The series was derived using diffusion Ai models and put together in a generative image composition on fx(hash). 

May 2022
150 editions were made available.

metadata.name: Shattered Moons #317
metadata.description:
ðŸŒ˜ðŸŒ—ðŸŒ–Shattered MoonsðŸŒ”ðŸŒ“ðŸŒ’

Explore deep space moons through this pure SVG generative experiment.

Features:
- Striped Background
- Shadows
- Vapors
- Horizontal Vapors
- Meteors
- Colored Meteors
- White Moon (0.5%)

SVG being a vectorial format, this work can be displayed/printed at any size.
Press 's' on Live View to save the SVG.
Press 'p' on Live View using a Chromium based browser to export as PNG.

Also, to fully enjoy your piece, I'd suggest to use a Chromium based browser as the SVG renderer gives more details.

metadata.name: Chord Unknown #222
metadata.description:
The feeling of experimenting with an instrument you have not learned, and then suddenly striking an actual chord.

The code creates several grids and then applies one of six unique deformation techniques with varying intensity. It's a defined process of experimentation, and even though I'm the one that wrote the rules, each output breaks through somehow as a complete surprise to me. So when I see them, I get a Chord Unknown.

Created by Eric Davidson. 2022.

metadata.name: Celestial Collisions  #786
metadata.description:
Celestial Collisions  - The following series is an exploration of organic textures that embodies the way of a gentle breeze and the simulation of color pencils that randomly generates simple shapes. Out of 380K different combinations of the following combinations,
an endless amount of orientations can be produced from the piece of work.  

For the interactivity element, turn on the (a)toms and check the pulsar settings.. on the interval the atoms will go from being almost invisible to standing front and center. Sometimes, you may need to look hard depending on the various atoms. 

* 's' - save an image of the current state 
* 'a' - activate atoms

The piece is to be experienced by default at 1000x1000, however, have fun with the image. It will adapt to various sizes and create different images by whatever size you view it in. 

@generatecoll 2021

metadata.name: Cold Mountain #284
metadata.description:
An impressionistic painting of a maintain on a foggy winter's day. The view will be of a mountain, mountain range, valley, or meadow. At nite, the lights come on, and the trees glow in the moonlight.

The image size is 928x1200. Press 's' to save a screenshot.

Common features:
- mountain size and stroke quality
- line quality of the trees
- 50/50 to have a spiral around the sun
- large palette with different application methods

Uncommon
- outline of the first mountain and sun
- amplified color/hue shifting

Rare
- nighttime
- no sun
